<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 3:44PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Anson
and Stanly Counties through 445 PM EDT...
At 344 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Marshville, or 13 miles northeast of Monroe, moving
northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Ansonville, Locust, Norwood, Badin, Oakboro, Stanfield,
Peachland, Morrow Mountain State Park and Lake Tillery.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
